// caches every built layer on disk forever, keyed by roothash; the
// reverse index from (pkg, version, suite, arch) → roothash is used
// to short-circuit BuildLayer when the result is already known.
//
// The roothash IS the layer's identity. Two BuildLayer calls with the
// same spec MUST return the same roothash (assuming the underlying
// .deb hasn't been re-uploaded upstream). This sidesteps the
// mkfs.ext4-reproducibility problem from the client-side build path
// (existing task #33): there is exactly one build per layer, done by
// the daemon, cached forever — clients never rebuild, they download.
//
