//   - Each LayerHandle carries a manifest.toml + manifest.sig where
//     the sig is RSA-PKCS1v15-SHA256 over manifest.toml under one of
//     the daemon's signing keys (selected by signing_key_id).
//   - The roothash inside the manifest.toml is the cryptographic
//     identity of image.img (verity root). Clients re-verify on
//     receipt: bytes are streamed → veritysetup format → compare
//     against manifest.toml's roothash.
//   - This means GetLayer transport can be untrusted (bytes are
//     content-addressed). But BuildLayer/BuildGeneration/UploadBlob
//     are bearer-token authenticated (same systemd-creds sealed
//     pattern as pancaked uses today; see DefaultSealedTokenPath in
//     internal/orchsrv).
//
// Out of scope for this service:
//   - `pancake-host` layer. Per-host by definition; clients build it
//     locally from inputs they shouldn't send to a shared cache.
//     Contents (post-rework):
//       /etc/hostname
//       /etc/machine-id                   (placeholder; systemd
//                                          regenerates at first boot)
//       /etc/ssh/ssh_host_*_key{,.pub}
//       /etc/ssh/sshd_config
//       /root/.ssh/authorized_keys
//       /etc/resolv.conf
//       /etc/systemd/network/10-wired.network
